<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880614-0009 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor: U.S. Census Bureau Can Keep a Secret </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GOVMT </CO><TEXT>   Re your page-one article &quot;Why Melinda S. Gets Ads for Panty Hose, Melinda F., Porsches&quot; (May 6): The article may be construed to mean the Census Bureau supplies mailing lists to the public, which is not the case.    For the record, Title 13, U.S. Code (Confidentiality), prohibits the Census Bureau from revealing any information about individuals or businesses. The bureau publishes only statistical totals.    James E. Gorman   Chief, Public Information Office   Bureau of the Census   Washington</TEXT></DOC>